1
00:00:00,667 --> 00:00:01,900
<i>- Hey!
- Let's-- Kiko!</i>

2
00:00:02,033 --> 00:00:02,967
<i> What are you doing, huh?</i>

3
00:00:03,100 --> 00:00:04,500
<i>You gonna call someone?
You gonna report us?</i>

4
00:00:04,633 --> 00:00:05,533
<i>- Stop it!
- What are you talking about?</i>

5
00:00:05,667 --> 00:00:07,800
<i>- You really can't be trusted!
- Kiko.</i>

6
00:00:07,933 --> 00:00:09,500
<i>You know what, Kiko?
You're getting on my nerves.</i>

7
00:00:09,633 --> 00:00:10,900
- Enough already. Can we just...
<i> - All you do</i>

8
00:00:11,033 --> 00:00:12,500
<i>- is accuse me of stuff!
- ...focus, please?</i>

9
00:00:12,633 --> 00:00:15,567
So what? You think I should just
<i> trust you right off the bat?</i>

10
00:00:15,700 --> 00:00:17,500
- [THUDS]
- [GRASS RUSTLING]

11
00:00:18,333 --> 00:00:20,867
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [GROANS IN PAIN]

12
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:23,833
[COUGHING]

13
00:00:26,900 --> 00:00:27,800
<i> Sari?</i>

14
00:00:29,067 --> 00:00:30,400
<i> Sari! Sari's gone missing.</i>

15
00:00:30,533 --> 00:00:32,467
<i>- Why didn't you wake me up?
- I'm so sorry!</i>

16
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:34,233
<i>- Sari?
- Sari!</i>

17
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:35,667
[SNIFFLES]

18
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:37,067
[SOBS SOFTLY]

19
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:39,333
<i> We're following the plan now.</i>

20
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:43,167
[SOBS SOFTLY]

21
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:46,200
- [MARTIN] Sari? Sari!
- [JUSTIN] Sari?

22
00:00:46,333 --> 00:00:49,467
- Sari! Sari!
- Sari!

23
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:51,300
- Sari!
- [SARI] Sir!

24
00:00:51,433 --> 00:00:53,333
Sa-- Sari, where are you?

25
00:00:53,467 --> 00:00:55,367
[SARI] Sir, I'm up here!

26
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:56,867
- Up there?
- What?

27
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:58,833
[ROPE STRAINING]

28
00:00:58,967 --> 00:01:00,400
- How'd you get up there?
- What is this?

29
00:01:00,533 --> 00:01:02,967
Sir,
can we talk about this later?

30
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:05,567
Just help me first, please!

31
00:01:05,700 --> 00:01:08,533
Hang on, I'll find a way
to get you down.

32
00:01:09,833 --> 00:01:11,800
- Justin, keep an eye on her.
- Yeah, sure, sure.

33
00:01:14,733 --> 00:01:16,600
Sir! Sir!

34
00:01:16,733 --> 00:01:18,133
- Sari?
- What happened?

35
00:01:18,267 --> 00:01:20,767
Sir, I found the shrine!
Look over there!

36
00:01:20,900 --> 00:01:23,500
There it is, sir!
Right there!

37
00:01:23,633 --> 00:01:25,300
Sari! Forget the shrine for now.

38
00:01:25,433 --> 00:01:27,367
We need to get you down first.

39
00:01:30,133 --> 00:01:36,933
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

40
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:32,833
[GRUNTS]

41
00:02:32,967 --> 00:02:34,033
[MARTIN] Well?

42
00:02:34,167 --> 00:02:36,033
I already tried, okay?
I can't reach it either.

43
00:02:37,233 --> 00:02:39,067
[CLICKS TONGUE]

44
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:40,833
[SARI]
Sir. Stop it, please.

45
00:02:40,967 --> 00:02:43,900
You might hurt yourself
trying to climb up there.

46
00:02:44,033 --> 00:02:47,267
We have to cut the rope up there
so you can get down.

47
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:50,200
Sir, just pass me the knife.

48
00:02:50,367 --> 00:02:51,433
What?

49
00:02:51,567 --> 00:02:54,367
Yes, sir. I'll do it.
I'll cut it myself.

50
00:02:54,500 --> 00:02:55,867
I can totally reach it.

51
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,433
Uh, just throw the knife
up to me. Toss it here.

52
00:02:58,567 --> 00:02:59,800
Come on, sir!

53
00:03:00,833 --> 00:03:02,800
No. It's too dangerous.
I can't do that.

54
00:03:02,933 --> 00:03:06,500
Sir, let's just try.
I'll catch it, I promise.

55
00:03:07,833 --> 00:03:09,267
Go.

56
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:11,467
Unless you have
a better idea?

57
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:13,433
[SARI] Sir, just trust me.

58
00:03:13,567 --> 00:03:14,867
[SARI GRUNTS]

59
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:18,900
If it doesn't work,
at least we tried, right?

60
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:23,900
Fine. Here it comes.

61
00:03:24,033 --> 00:03:25,233
Okay.

62
00:03:25,367 --> 00:03:27,933
One, two, three.

63
00:03:28,067 --> 00:03:29,200
Sir, toss it here.

64
00:03:29,333 --> 00:03:30,667
- [GRUNTS] One more time, sir.
- Ugh. Again, one more time.

65
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:32,600
- Let me try that again.
- One more.

66
00:03:32,733 --> 00:03:36,567
Here we go, okay?
One... two... three!

67
00:03:37,633 --> 00:03:40,667
Hold on, sir.
Keep going, throw it higher.

68
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,867
You can do it. Try again.

69
00:03:44,233 --> 00:03:47,233
One, two, three!

70
00:03:47,367 --> 00:03:49,367
- Yes! Okay!
- Sir, I got it!

71
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:52,633
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

72
00:03:52,767 --> 00:03:53,867
- Okay.
- Good, take it slow.

73
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,900
- Just wait right there, sir.
- Alright.

74
00:03:56,867 --> 00:03:59,433
Hold on, sir.
I'm coming down.

75
00:03:59,567 --> 00:04:01,167
Wait for me there, sir.

76
00:04:07,633 --> 00:04:09,233
- Take it easy, okay?
- Sari, be careful.

77
00:04:09,367 --> 00:04:11,100
Go slow, alright?

78
00:04:11,233 --> 00:04:13,367
Hold on, Sir Martin, wait--
[ROPE SNAPS]

79
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:14,800
[SCREAMING]

80
00:04:16,033 --> 00:04:17,533
- [SCREAMING CONTINUES]
- Sari!

81
00:04:17,667 --> 00:04:19,533
[BODY THUDS]

82
00:04:19,667 --> 00:04:26,633
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

83
00:04:33,700 --> 00:04:34,700
[CLAPS] Hey!

84
00:04:34,833 --> 00:04:36,767
Oh... S-Sir. I'm sorry, sir.

85
00:04:36,900 --> 00:04:39,167
- I'm so sorry.
- Come on.

86
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:40,900
[CHUCKLES] Mm-hmm.

87
00:04:43,567 --> 00:04:44,933
[EXHALES SOFTLY]

88
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:50,000
You here all alone?

89
00:04:51,533 --> 00:04:53,567
Yeah, for a long time now.

90
00:04:53,700 --> 00:04:56,533
My mom died
when I was just a kid.

91
00:04:56,667 --> 00:04:59,333
She left me with my grandma,
but...

92
00:04:59,467 --> 00:05:01,267
she didn't live long either.

93
00:05:04,767 --> 00:05:06,867
Why are you digging up
my grandma's grave?

94
00:05:08,267 --> 00:05:09,333
Uh...

95
00:05:11,267 --> 00:05:12,367
Because...

96
00:05:14,367 --> 00:05:15,500
We're looking for a clue.

97
00:05:15,633 --> 00:05:19,100
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

98
00:05:19,233 --> 00:05:22,133
We found coordinates
at your house.

99
00:05:23,433 --> 00:05:27,233
And the directions led straight
to your grandma's grave.

100
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:32,667
We don't know why
it's here either.

101
00:05:36,233 --> 00:05:37,267
A clue?

102
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:41,733
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

103
00:05:41,867 --> 00:05:44,433
We don't mean you any harm.

104
00:05:44,567 --> 00:05:48,800
We're doing all this because my
brother's life is in danger.

105
00:05:48,933 --> 00:05:52,467
Truth is, they're moving
her brother to another prison,

106
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:54,400
she couldn't say goodbye.

107
00:05:54,533 --> 00:05:58,033
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

108
00:05:58,167 --> 00:06:01,267
But I chose to come here
and find this clue,

109
00:06:02,267 --> 00:06:04,633
so we can prove
who's really guilty.

110
00:06:04,767 --> 00:06:11,200
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

111
00:06:11,367 --> 00:06:17,733
[ENGINE REVVING]

112
00:06:20,100 --> 00:06:21,533
[OFFICER 1]
Sir, we're stuck in traffic.

113
00:06:21,667 --> 00:06:24,533
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

114
00:06:24,667 --> 00:06:25,833
Are we far from there yet?

115
00:06:25,967 --> 00:06:27,167
[OFFICER 1]
Still pretty far, sir.

116
00:06:29,933 --> 00:06:32,867
"You won't be safe
once you reach the city jail."

117
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:41,833
[MUSIC BECOMES GRIM]

118
00:06:58,567 --> 00:07:04,533
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

119
00:07:04,667 --> 00:07:07,733
[HANDCUFFS CLICKING]

120
00:07:07,867 --> 00:07:14,767
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

121
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,600
A life is on the line here.

122
00:07:33,733 --> 00:07:37,833
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

123
00:07:37,967 --> 00:07:39,733
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

124
00:07:40,633 --> 00:07:42,867
Alright, go ahead and dig.

125
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,133
Find whatever
you're looking for.

126
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,433
[LUNA] Thank you.

127
00:07:51,633 --> 00:07:52,900
[GUN CLICKS]

128
00:07:53,033 --> 00:07:55,367
Don't you move!
I'll shoot him!

129
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:56,500
Put that down!

130
00:07:56,633 --> 00:07:58,200
Open the door
or I'll kill him!

131
00:07:58,333 --> 00:08:00,533
- [OFFICER 2] Put it down!
- Open the door!

132
00:08:00,667 --> 00:08:02,200
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

133
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:09,133
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

134
00:08:10,767 --> 00:08:12,067
Hey! Wait.

135
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:14,067
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

136
00:08:15,567 --> 00:08:16,833
- [OFFICER 1] Sir!
- Sir!

137
00:08:16,967 --> 00:08:19,400
- Hey, put the gun down!
- [OFFICER 3] Drop it!

138
00:08:19,533 --> 00:08:20,867
- Sir!
- Oh!

139
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:25,067
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

140
00:08:25,233 --> 00:08:27,267
- Run! Go now!
- What?

141
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:28,533
[BODY THUDS]

142
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:34,733
- Hey!
- [GUNSHOTS]

143
00:08:34,867 --> 00:08:38,300
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

144
00:08:41,333 --> 00:08:42,567
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

145
00:08:43,700 --> 00:08:46,833
Radio the other unit.
We need to wait for backup.

146
00:08:46,967 --> 00:08:48,367
We're gonna surround this place.

147
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:49,533
Yes, sir.

148
00:08:53,367 --> 00:08:59,433
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

149
00:09:01,867 --> 00:09:03,467
Syvera, what happened?

150
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:05,300
Leon Almazan escaped.

151
00:09:05,433 --> 00:09:06,800
We need to find him.

152
00:09:07,633 --> 00:09:09,400
Alright. Let's go.

153
00:09:12,300 --> 00:09:15,967
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

154
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:23,000
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

155
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:37,000
Leon!

156
00:09:37,133 --> 00:09:44,067
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

157
00:09:48,967 --> 00:09:52,900
Vito's dead. He died just days
after coming to see you.

158
00:09:53,733 --> 00:09:54,633
What?

159
00:09:54,767 --> 00:09:56,567
[PANTING]

160
00:09:56,700 --> 00:10:00,533
De La Paz paid someone inside
city jail to silence you.

161
00:10:01,667 --> 00:10:04,667
So De La Paz is the accomplice
you were talking about.

162
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:05,800
I believe you now.

163
00:10:05,933 --> 00:10:07,900
You had nothing to do
with Juan's murder.

164
00:10:08,033 --> 00:10:12,733
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

165
00:10:12,867 --> 00:10:15,267
Run. Go on.

166
00:10:18,733 --> 00:10:19,900
Hurry.

167
00:10:22,767 --> 00:10:24,133
[GUN CLICKS]

168
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:26,467
Come on!

169
00:10:28,667 --> 00:10:29,833
[SARI] This is it!

170
00:10:29,967 --> 00:10:32,400
We're here, sir.
This is the spot.

171
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:35,400
Whoa.

172
00:10:37,100 --> 00:10:39,300
What are we even supposed
to look for here?

173
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:41,633
Anything.

174
00:10:41,767 --> 00:10:43,233
Anything that can help us,

175
00:10:43,367 --> 00:10:46,433
or anything that tells us
about the treasure.

176
00:10:46,567 --> 00:10:48,100
Aren't we going to dig?

177
00:10:48,233 --> 00:10:49,800
That's what Luna and I
did last time.

178
00:10:49,933 --> 00:10:52,867
Sir, this place is sacred.

179
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:55,067
We can't just dig
anywhere we want.

180
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:57,767
If we don't dig, how will we
ever find where the treasure is?

181
00:10:57,900 --> 00:10:59,133
As I said before,

182
00:10:59,267 --> 00:11:02,467
let's look for clues first.
A mark, a drawing.

183
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:05,667
Anything that shows us exactly
where the treasure is hidden.

184
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:07,033
Plus this place is huge.

185
00:11:07,167 --> 00:11:09,200
We'd never be able to dig up
every inch.

186
00:11:11,633 --> 00:11:13,367
Let's start.

187
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:14,533
Okay.

188
00:11:14,667 --> 00:11:21,000
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

189
00:11:21,833 --> 00:11:22,933
[GRUNTS]

190
00:11:23,067 --> 00:11:26,800
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

191
00:11:26,933 --> 00:11:28,333
[GRUNTS]

192
00:11:28,467 --> 00:11:35,233
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

193
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:44,467
[MUSIC BECOMES GRIM]

194
00:11:44,633 --> 00:11:46,300
Almazan!
[GUNSHOT]

195
00:11:49,533 --> 00:11:50,500
[GUN CLICKS]

196
00:11:50,633 --> 00:11:57,400
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

197
00:12:05,467 --> 00:12:07,933
[GUN CLICKS] You're not getting
away from me, Almazan.

198
00:12:09,300 --> 00:12:10,100
Ah!

199
00:12:10,233 --> 00:12:11,967
- [KICK LANDS]
- [GROANS]

200
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:13,633
[BOTH GRUNTING]

201
00:12:13,767 --> 00:12:15,533
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [GROANS IN PAIN]

202
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:18,300
[GRUNTING]

203
00:12:19,733 --> 00:12:21,033
[YELPS, BODY THUDS]

204
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:24,267
[GRUNTS]

205
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:26,367
- [KICK LANDS]
- [GROANS IN PAIN]

206
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:29,100
[GUN CLICKS, GUNSHOT]

207
00:12:30,367 --> 00:12:31,333
[GRUNTS]

208
00:12:31,467 --> 00:12:38,233
- [LEAVES CRUNCHING]
- [GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

209
00:12:38,367 --> 00:12:39,967
[MUSIC FADES]

210
00:12:56,867 --> 00:12:59,167
[RUSTLING]

211
00:13:01,933 --> 00:13:03,200
[HOLLOW THUDDING]

212
00:13:04,100 --> 00:13:06,200
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

213
00:13:06,333 --> 00:13:07,433
Justin!

214
00:13:07,567 --> 00:13:12,767
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

215
00:13:12,900 --> 00:13:14,167
What is it?

216
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:17,700
[GRUNTING]

217
00:13:17,833 --> 00:13:19,800
[BLOCK OF WOOD RATTLES SLIGHTLY]

218
00:13:19,933 --> 00:13:21,733
[GRUNTS]

219
00:13:21,900 --> 00:13:22,967
Oh.

220
00:13:23,100 --> 00:13:27,300
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

221
00:13:27,433 --> 00:13:28,633
What's that?

222
00:13:31,900 --> 00:13:33,300
Looks like a map?

223
00:13:34,567 --> 00:13:37,400
Take a photo right now!
Hurry, snap a picture!

224
00:13:37,533 --> 00:13:38,567
Wait.

225
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:42,100
[JUSTIN]
Make sure it's clear, okay?

226
00:13:42,233 --> 00:13:45,167
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

227
00:13:45,300 --> 00:13:46,533
[MARTIN]
Let's take another one.

228
00:13:46,667 --> 00:13:48,100
- [JUSTIN] Perfect.
- [CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

229
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:50,567
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

230
00:13:50,700 --> 00:13:57,500
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

231
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:07,567
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

232
00:14:09,067 --> 00:14:10,033
Where's Almazan?

233
00:14:10,167 --> 00:14:11,933
Shoot! He slipped away from me!

234
00:14:12,067 --> 00:14:13,500
Where? Which way did he go?

235
00:14:13,633 --> 00:14:15,067
He headed toward Ilaya!

236
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,833
Radio all units near that area.

237
00:14:16,967 --> 00:14:19,400
He's not going to get far.
I shot him.

238
00:14:19,533 --> 00:14:20,967
You shot him?
Where'd you hit him?

239
00:14:21,100 --> 00:14:22,333
His shoulder.

240
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:26,500
[LEAVES CRUNCHING]

241
00:14:26,633 --> 00:14:28,133
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

242
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:33,933
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

243
00:14:34,067 --> 00:14:35,600
Surround the whole island.

244
00:14:35,733 --> 00:14:38,267
Call the coast guard.
He might try to escape by boat.

245
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:39,867
We can't let him get away.

246
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,367
- Let's go!
- Let's go.

247
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:46,500
[GRUNTING HARD]

248
00:14:48,067 --> 00:14:48,967
Found anything?

249
00:14:51,133 --> 00:14:52,000
Nope.

250
00:14:53,133 --> 00:14:54,300
[GIO GRUNTS]

251
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:58,000
Well? Have they messaged us?

252
00:14:59,167 --> 00:15:00,767
How about we go home for now?

253
00:15:02,133 --> 00:15:03,667
We haven't found anything yet.

254
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:05,700
Exactly.
We haven't found anything.

255
00:15:05,833 --> 00:15:07,867
What if the coordinates
are wrong again?

256
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:10,467
What if it's not here?

257
00:15:11,100 --> 00:15:12,267
This is the right place.

258
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:13,667
We just need to keep looking.

259
00:15:13,800 --> 00:15:16,000
And remember,
this is for your brother.

260
00:15:17,533 --> 00:15:18,733
I'm just curious.

261
00:15:18,867 --> 00:15:21,233
The clue you have...
the one with the coordinates...

262
00:15:21,367 --> 00:15:22,533
Where did you get it?

263
00:15:23,433 --> 00:15:24,567
We inherited it.

264
00:15:25,633 --> 00:15:27,133
My father left it for us.

265
00:15:27,633 --> 00:15:29,800
Your father?
What was his name?

266
00:15:30,433 --> 00:15:31,533
Mike.

267
00:15:32,133 --> 00:15:33,467
Michael Fernandez.

268
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:37,067
Mike from Solara Island?

269
00:15:37,433 --> 00:15:39,000
Your Mister Mike's son?

270
00:15:40,333 --> 00:15:41,500
You knew my father?

271
00:15:41,633 --> 00:15:43,867
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

272
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:44,867
[PABLO EXHALES DEEPLY]

273
00:15:45,667 --> 00:15:47,133
Is this what you're looking for?

274
00:15:51,967 --> 00:15:53,967
[SOIL CRUNCHING]

275
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:54,967
[THUDS]

276
00:15:55,100 --> 00:16:00,033
- [STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [PABLO PANTING]

277
00:16:03,333 --> 00:16:04,767
I think it is.

278
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:12,833
[PHONE CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING]

279
00:16:15,267 --> 00:16:16,167
[GIO GRUNTS]

280
00:16:20,167 --> 00:16:21,733
But why is it here at...

281
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:25,067
Paloma Ruiz's grave?

282
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:27,667
She knew everything.

283
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:29,600
My grandmother.

284
00:16:32,233 --> 00:16:33,867
"Oro Viejo."

285
00:16:34,733 --> 00:16:37,067
That's what she used to tell me.

286
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:39,233
[LUNA] But why does it look
like that?

287
00:16:39,667 --> 00:16:40,800
Is it supposed to be a map?

288
00:16:41,467 --> 00:16:42,500
It doesn't look like one.

289
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:45,333
She said it's just a part
of a bigger map.

290
00:16:45,467 --> 00:16:46,967
I don't know if it's true.

291
00:16:47,667 --> 00:16:49,867
She was so obsessed
with Oro Viejo

292
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,833
that she asked for it to be
placed on her tombstone

293
00:16:51,967 --> 00:16:53,100
before she died.

294
00:16:53,233 --> 00:16:55,000
But she asked you to place it...

295
00:16:55,133 --> 00:16:56,200
Underneath.

296
00:16:56,933 --> 00:17:00,133
She didn't want
greedy treasure hunters

297
00:17:00,267 --> 00:17:02,200
swarming her grave.

298
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:05,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

299
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:07,500
But why did you tell my father?

300
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:12,100
He explained why the treasure
mattered so much to him.

301
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:15,867
He said it was
for his loved ones.

302
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:21,200
After that, he became one of
the people who looked after me.

303
00:17:22,767 --> 00:17:23,700
How?

304
00:17:24,433 --> 00:17:27,200
He'd come here
to bring me food

305
00:17:27,333 --> 00:17:29,167
and have a chat with me
sometimes.

306
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:32,700
Until one day.
he stopped coming back.

307
00:17:33,300 --> 00:17:34,967
I tried to find him.

308
00:17:35,300 --> 00:17:36,633
I went to the island.

309
00:17:37,467 --> 00:17:39,900
That's where I heard he died.

310
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:43,667
He died because of the treasure.

311
00:17:45,267 --> 00:17:48,333
And now that you've found this,
your lives are in danger too.

312
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:50,000
So be careful.

313
00:17:51,267 --> 00:17:53,367
[LUNA] Thank you so much, uh...

314
00:17:53,500 --> 00:17:54,667
Pablo.

315
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:57,100
Thank you, Pablo.

316
00:17:58,067 --> 00:18:00,233
Thank you for
saving my life as well.

317
00:18:00,367 --> 00:18:07,000
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

318
00:18:15,467 --> 00:18:16,933
[ANDY EXHALES DEEPLY]

319
00:18:26,667 --> 00:18:33,633
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

320
00:18:41,933 --> 00:18:44,667
[CLANKING]

321
00:18:48,667 --> 00:18:53,067
[PHONE RINGING]

322
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:07,367
[MARINA ON THE OTHER LINE]
<i> Sir, Leon escaped.</i>

323
00:19:07,500 --> 00:19:09,300
<i>My colleagues are
looking for him.</i>

324
00:19:09,433 --> 00:19:12,167
<i>If we don't find him,
our plan could fall apart!</i>

325
00:19:13,067 --> 00:19:14,800
<i>Should I proceed
to Plan B, sir?</i>

326
00:19:14,933 --> 00:19:19,067
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

327
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:20,167
Edward!

328
00:19:20,833 --> 00:19:22,967
- [MARINA]<i> Hello? Sir?
</i>- Why are you touching my stuff?

329
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:27,267
The police is reporting to you
about Leon?!

330
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:28,400
[ANDY] Edward, bud...

331
00:19:28,567 --> 00:19:30,100
Is it because you're the one
who had him locked up?

332
00:19:30,233 --> 00:19:34,400
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

333
00:19:34,533 --> 00:19:36,633
Did you kill Juan as well?

334
00:19:37,633 --> 00:19:38,867
No.

335
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:41,033
- Are you a murderer, Dad?
- No. N-No. Of course not!

336
00:19:41,633 --> 00:19:43,300
I didn't kill Juan.

337
00:19:47,033 --> 00:19:49,000
- Edward, wait!
- Let me go!

338
00:19:49,133 --> 00:19:50,000
- Wait!
- What?!

339
00:19:50,933 --> 00:19:52,767
Are you finally going
to tell me the truth?

340
00:19:54,467 --> 00:19:55,667
The truth is...

341
00:19:56,300 --> 00:19:58,967
I had nothing to do
with Juan's death.

342
00:19:59,467 --> 00:20:02,200
Until you tell me the truth...

343
00:20:04,367 --> 00:20:06,733
forget that you have a son.

344
00:20:07,667 --> 00:20:08,733
Edward--

345
00:20:09,367 --> 00:20:10,867
Edward, wait!

346
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:12,233
[ANDY] I'm talking to you!

347
00:20:13,033 --> 00:20:13,733
Edward!

348
00:20:13,867 --> 00:20:17,233
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

349
00:20:18,933 --> 00:20:21,100
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [PHONE THUDS]

350
00:20:21,733 --> 00:20:23,000
[FRIDA] Leon?

351
00:20:23,767 --> 00:20:25,500
- Mom? Mom?
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]

352
00:20:25,633 --> 00:20:27,300
- Mom, why?
- Leon...

353
00:20:27,933 --> 00:20:30,200
The... The police called.

354
00:20:30,333 --> 00:20:31,533
Leon escaped.

355
00:20:31,667 --> 00:20:32,700
What?!

356
00:20:33,267 --> 00:20:34,700
Leon escaped?!

357
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:36,933
Why did Leon do that?

358
00:20:37,700 --> 00:20:39,333
This is not good.

359
00:20:39,467 --> 00:20:41,467
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

360
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:43,933
Thank you for your help

361
00:20:44,067 --> 00:20:46,433
even after all the trouble
we brought you.

362
00:20:46,567 --> 00:20:48,133
Wait. What about the...

363
00:20:49,067 --> 00:20:51,233
Don't worry about it.
I'll take care of them.

364
00:20:52,767 --> 00:20:55,700
I hope you find Oro Viejo
for your brother's sake.

365
00:20:57,167 --> 00:20:59,933
I'm sorry about
Mister Mike's death.

366
00:21:00,633 --> 00:21:02,433
He was a good man
just like you.

367
00:21:02,567 --> 00:21:05,133
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

368
00:21:05,267 --> 00:21:06,133
Thank you.

369
00:21:09,333 --> 00:21:10,233
Let's go.

370
00:21:18,733 --> 00:21:19,533
[MARTIN] Thank you.

371
00:21:20,067 --> 00:21:21,333
[JUSTIN EXHALES DEEPLY]

372
00:21:21,467 --> 00:21:22,467
[SARI] Thank you.

373
00:21:27,167 --> 00:21:28,167
Sir.

374
00:21:28,700 --> 00:21:30,600
We've accomplished
our mission, right?

375
00:21:30,733 --> 00:21:31,900
I think so.

376
00:21:32,033 --> 00:21:34,233
What we found
could be a huge deal.

377
00:21:35,967 --> 00:21:37,533
[RAPHIE] Sir, thank goodness
you're finally back.

378
00:21:37,667 --> 00:21:39,033
Why? Did something happen?

379
00:21:39,167 --> 00:21:40,833
Gio and Luna still aren't back.

380
00:21:40,967 --> 00:21:43,067
Tsk. Did they stay somewhere
overnight too?

381
00:21:43,233 --> 00:21:44,967
I honestly hope
that's all it is.

382
00:21:45,100 --> 00:21:46,767
and that nothing happened
to them.

383
00:21:47,767 --> 00:21:48,833
Martin!

384
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:50,533
Jade called.

385
00:21:50,667 --> 00:21:51,700
She said Leon escaped.

386
00:21:51,833 --> 00:21:52,733
What?!

387
00:21:52,867 --> 00:21:57,333
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

388
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:01,900
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

389
00:22:02,033 --> 00:22:04,500
[GROANING IN PAIN]

390
00:22:09,233 --> 00:22:11,333
[GROANS IN PAIN]

391
00:22:11,467 --> 00:22:13,333
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

392
00:22:13,467 --> 00:22:20,133
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

393
00:22:20,833 --> 00:22:21,800
[GROANING IN PAIN]

394
00:22:22,533 --> 00:22:23,433
<i> Edward!</i>

395
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:24,967
<i> I'm sorry, Jade.</i>

396
00:22:25,933 --> 00:22:27,267
<i>- Let's go!
- Just leave me, Martin!</i>

397
00:22:27,667 --> 00:22:29,267
<i> I don't want them to worry.</i>

398
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:31,567
<i> So please! Just go.</i>

399
00:22:31,700 --> 00:22:33,600
<i> Auntie, I met with your son.</i>

400
00:22:34,067 --> 00:22:35,367
<i> Is he okay?</i>

401
00:22:35,667 --> 00:22:37,533
<i> He's... He's fine.</i>

402
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:40,367
[BODY THUDS]

403
00:22:41,533 --> 00:22:43,867
<i> Leon, hang in there.</i>

404
00:22:44,367 --> 00:22:46,067
<i>You still have
to go back to them.</i>

405
00:22:48,567 --> 00:22:48,967
<i> Aah!</i>
